<p style="text-align: center">
<span class="PRTitle"><!-- NewsTitle.start -->TRANSCRIPT OF AMBUSH INTERVIEW 
<br />
WITH SEN BONGBONG MARCOS, JR<!-- NewsTitle.end --></span>
</p>
<!-- NewsBody.start -->
<p style="text-align: justify">ON EDUCATION (SCUs &amp; LUCs)</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Q: Sir, any update sa hearing today on education?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">SEN BONGBONG MARCOS: We are trying to get information sa sitwasyon ng  SUCs and LUCs -their registration and accreditation with the CHED. Sa simula  pa lang , ang  kailangan nating  gawin ay malaman kung  ano ba talaga ang sitwasyon? Ilan  ba talaga ang mga eskwelang na  itinayo na  hindi na-accredit ? Kung ano ba ang standard nila? Para  naman yun mga  estudyanteng nag-aaral  ay paglabas  yun kanilang diploma ay  may kabuluhan at kinikilala. Kung mag-take sila ng examination kailangan galing sila sa accredited  school-- kung hindi accredited, hindi  sila papayagang mag-board exams.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Kailangan talagang ma-regulate ng mabuti ang bagay na ito at pagkatapos  nating malaman kung ano ang mga nagyayari sa sistema at kung ano pa ang pwede nating magawang tulong.  Kasi  kung minsan ang  LGU ay nagtatayo  ng local university or college  (LUC) at yan ay itinatayo nila dahil sa kanilang pananaw na kulang ang mga eskuwelahan  sa kanilang mga lugar. Yung iba naman ay nagtatayo lamang ng eskwelahan para  gawing negosyo. Kaya kailangan nating pag-aralan kung sino ang naghahanap ng paraan para mabigyan ng edukasyon ang kanilang mga constituents  at kung sino yun iba  na pinagkakikitaan lamang kaya  hindi nagiging maganda ang level ng edukasyon.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Kapag nalaman  na natin kung ano ang sitwasyon, dahan-dahan  na natin pagandahin at baguhin ang sistema and probably  even  add subsidies if possible to those  who are accredited  and registered with the CHED as  LUCs and at the same time for  the State Universities and Colleges (SUCs)</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Q: Sir, alam na ba natin kung ilang ang accredited ng CHED sa mga  local universities and colleges?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">SBBM: Hindi nga eh. Most are not although yung  mga malalaki at mga kilala are doing very well at saka malaki  ang naitutulong nila dahil parang dagdag  nga dito sa ating mga  university at  college pero yun iba ay hindi alam kung ilan na nga ba talaga sila na nagpapa-aral na hindi naman kinikilala ng CHED. Malaking problema yun.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Doon sa hearing, hiningi ng committee  sa ating mga  resource persons kung ano  yung record. At tingnan natin, isa-isahin nating pag-aralan kung yung mga non-registered kung paano naman ang kanilang patakbo doon sa kanilang mga paaralan. Kung maganda ang nagiging resulta? Kung talagang natuturuan yun mga estudyante?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Q: Ginagamit  lang daw ng mga politician sa probinsya?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">SBBM:  I don't know if that's the case. I think most of the cases ay nine-negosyo lamang at  pinagkakakitaan lamang. Ngunit  ang mga local government unit  ay talagang naghahanap ng paraan para yun kakulangan ng facilities for education sa tertiary level ay madagdagan at handa naman silang magbayad, meron naman silang pondo--yun mga ganun ay tulungan natin.  We have to determine kung  ano nga ang naging patakbo doon sa iba't-ibang eskwelahan. We have to identify those  who have  done a  good job  of providing  quality education, those who are merely a commercial enterprise even a political enterprise.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">ON ARMM POLL POSTPONEMENT</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Q: Sir, nagkaroon ng consensus kahapon sa Ledac  meeting na parang ipa-prioritize yun postponement ng ARMM elections so as chairman ng committee on Local Government ano ang reaction nyo sir?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">SBBM: Many of our friends from ARMM both the congressmen--yun mga governor hindi ko pa nakausap pero yun 2 nakausap ko na,   they are making their sentiments and  opinions known that it is the preference of most of the political leaders in ARMM that there be  an election. If there is a postponement, let the postponement be for just maybe a few  weeks or  at the most for  few months. Ayaw naman nilang magpa-holdover. Handa naman silang  magkaroon ng halalan.  The congressmen from ARMM and the governors will meet with the president and they will make their case as to what  in their opinion should be done. Hopefully from those discussion (ledac meeting) that  there will be a breakthrough  but right now the positions of  the ARMM political leadership  and the Palace are not the same.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Q:  Ikaw  sir, anong personal position nyo?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">SBBM: I think it is a good thing in principle that if there is to be an election, that we have the election. If for example , for operational reason-  hindi pa handa  yun machine, hindi pa na-impreta ang balota, if the operational problems then postponement is alright but  only for such  time as  those operational problems can be resolved.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Sabihin na natin  na papayag tayo ng ilang  linggo  to give the Comelec  more of a chance to do  whatever it is that they have to do. But  in principle we should always take this view towards the idea that if there is an election we should conduct it. That way, there is not question that the political leadership has in fact that mandate.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">There is also a possibility of  the appointees as proposed by the palace  not to be  recognized by  the local leaders and  they have actually said that. Sinabi nila, kung i-a-appoint yan at hindi naman namin kinikilala, we will not recognize them and this will cause  a great deal of confusion and it might deteriorate into complete political chaos down in ARMM. So, must line the compromise arrangement where the political leaders of ARMM still have that mandate  so that they will able to  go to the people  and present the initiative and  that leadership  will not be questioned.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Q: Sir  sa part ninyo, consultation  pa lang ang ginagawa? Wala pang hearing dahil wala pang bill?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">SBBM; Wala pang nag-file sa Senado. The bill has been filed in the House. Tapos na ang kanilang hearing at sabi nila yun committee report  baka lalabas next  week at pupunta na sa plenary.  But essentially, the issue now is between the Palace   and the ARMM leadership and we must try to find common ground between the two positions. But right now, it is hard to see what that common ground is dahil malalayo pa ang  kanilang mga position. We will see what will happen after the discussion between the President and the ARMM leadership.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Q:  Considering  na ganun ang stand ng majority ng local officials sa ARMM, posibleng mahirap  kung ang proposal ay postponement until 2013?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">SBBM: Well, kung talagang tututulan nila ng husto ,and so far they are doing that, ay  mahihirapan talaga. May mga questions of law, halimbawa yun pag-appoint  to change the law,  you need  2/3 of the Congress, hindi  sila nag public hearing , what is the  legal basis of appointing? Yun ang mga problema sa ngayon. There  are many problems at the political level and at the legal level and this have to  be ironed out.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Q: Makakaya ba sir? sa August na yun ARMM elections?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">SBBM: Kaya nga, kung ganito ang magiging usapan  at napakalayo pa ng mga iba't-ibang grupo sa kanilang mga position ay baka matagalan pa. Ang sabi sa akin ni former chairman Melo, it will require 4 to 5 months to get the ballots printed. We also haven't made the decision as to whether or not the PCOS machine will be bought for the ARMM elections.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">We have  extended our deadline for the rest of this year so we have that time but the small substantive issues still have to be resolved whether or not we will  postpone, whether or not there  will be appointments.  All of these things have to...before  we even  make a decision to continue with the  election before  we even start making preparations for the elections.  Marami pang gagawin. It is acceptable, I think to all that we postpone to take  care of all these issues but still with ... to conducting those elections  as soon and as quickly as possible  and I think the idea of appointing  the leadership is the one that is going  to be a  very ,very difficult issue to be resolved because there are very few arguments    that   have been heard that make the case  properly for the  appointment of the political leaders of the ARMM.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">THANK YOU.</p>
